data.title: Rahul Mahajan to participate in 'MasterChef 3'?
data.meta_description: If sources are to be believed Rahul Mahajan is all set to become a foodie by participating in MasterChef 3. Rahul Mahajan has participated in different reality shows like Rahul Dulhaniya Le Jayega, Bigg Boss-2, Comedy Circus and recently in Nach Baliye.

Urvashi Rautela Faces Backlash Over Paris Video Featuring Controversial Dress

Urvashi Rautela's recent Instagram video from Paris has attracted significant backlash. The clip features her wearing a custom-designed Duena shirt-dress by MaisonJ Simone, which includes images of Mother Mary. The inclusion of religious imagery in the outfit has sparked controversy, leading many viewers to express their anger in the comments section. According to reports, an organisation has urged the Maharashtra government to take action against Rautela, demanding that she face charges for offending religious sentiments. In response, the actress posted a clarification note on social media, and an apology from Urvashi was reportedly conveyed through her spokesperson. On the work front, Urvashi is currently receiving praise for her performance in Ghuspaithiya.

Abhishek Bachchan, Malaika Arora, and More Watch Neeraj Chopra Win Silver at Paris Olympics

Neeraj Chopra made history by clinching silver at the Paris Olympics, and the achievement was met with widespread acclaim from fans and celebrities alike. Social media was flooded with praise for him, with notable figures like Vicky Kaushal, Randeep Hooda, Sunny Deol, and many others extending their congratulations online. In addition to virtual support, some celebrities traveled to Paris to cheer Neeraj on from the Olympic stadium. Abhishek Bachchan, Malaika Arora, and other stars witnessed Neerajâ€™s performance live. Malaika, seen in a viral video wearing a beige outfit and hat, shared her pride on Instagram after Neeraj's win. Abhishek posted clips of Neeraj on his Instagram Stories and also shared a photo from the Paris stadium, proudly holding the tricolor. Lara Dutta, who was at the Paris Olympics with her husband Mahesh Bhupathi, daughter Saira, and friends, also posted multiple photos on Instagram from the event.
